    let n_t = words n_temp
    let n = read $ n_t!!0 :: Int
    let q = read $ n_t!!1 :: Int
    nodes_temp <- getLine
    let nodes = map read $ words nodes_temp :: [Int]
    edges_temp <- getMultipleLines n-1
    let edges = map ( map ( read :: String -> Int ) . words ) edges_temp
    forM_ [1..q] $ \a0  -> do
        u_temp <- getLine
        let u = read u_temp :: Int
        v_temp <- getLine
        let v = read v_temp :: Int
        -- your code goes here


getMultipleLines :: Int -> IO [String]

getMultipleLines n
    | n <= 0 = return []
    | otherwise = do          
        x <- getLine         
        xs <- getMultipleLines (n-1)    
        let ret = (x:xs)    
        return ret

n,q = io.read("*number", "*number", "*l")
nodes = {}
nodes_temp = io.read()
nodes_i = 1;
for token in string.gmatch(nodes_temp, "[^%s]+") do
	nodes[nodes_i] = token
	nodes_i = nodes_i + 1
end
edges = {}
for edges_i = 1,n-1 do
	edges_temp = io.read()
	edges_j = 1

end
